args:
Separated from Alfonse, Veronica visits a
nearby village and comes across Loki, who
takes her away after promising to help recover
her memory. Meanwhile, the party meets 
the Hero-King Marth, and together they set
off in pursuit of Veronica.
Even though I told him I'd never\nforgive him if he was lying.
Don't you know it's dangerous here?\nThere are imperial soldiers about!
Oh dear. Have you been separated\nfrom your family?
Well, whoever he is, he seems important\nto you, which is all that matters.
I've also been waiting for someone\na long time, so perhaps you should\ncome along with me.
There's a village not all that far from here.\nIf you're going to be waiting, you might\nas well do it in relative safety.
There's a powerful swordsman there\nwho will certainly keep you safe.
I won't hear another word on the matter.\nYou're coming with me, and that's that!
You know me too? No fair.\nI don't remember you.
I am Marth, Prince of Altea—though I\nwager that means little to you at present.
Is this girl an acquaintance of yours,\ngood sir knight?

How lucky you are, girl; this kind
swordsman has sworn to protect our
village from that most terrible Empire,
and I'm sure he'll do the same for you!
Are you really that nice?\nJust like him...
I will not stand idly by while injustice\ngoes unpunished. But if I may ask,\nwho did you mean by ＂him＂?
He said he'd come after me.
Then I am certain he will; Prince Alfonse\nis not a man who takes his oaths lightly.

I would also like to see him, and I believe
waiting here would be more effective than
engaging in some wild, fruitless search.
I pray you will join me.
AAUUGH! THE IMPERIAL ARMY IS HERE!
If they would seek to rule by force,\nI shall stand against them.
...Oh, my.\nI'm not here to do anything like that.
I wouldn't DARE challenge the great\nHero-King—I'm simply here to collect\nour distinguished guest.
Tee hee! It's been a while, Marth.
I would SO very much love to invite you\nto the party, but I'm afraid I simply must\nescort someone else.
I take it your sights are set on\nPrincess Veronica, then?
Ooo, what a clever boy you are!\n...Now come along, Veronica.
You wound me! And after ALL the\nadventures we've been through together.
Why, I know the feelings in your heart\nbetter than you do yourself.
You are uneasy, no? Your memories lost,\nadrift in a strange and unfamiliar land,\nseparated from the person you relied on...
I can rid you of that unease.\nI can restore your memories.
You mustn't believe her honeyed words!
Now now, Hero-King. I speak only the\ntruth; I CAN help restore her memory.
And should you reclaim your strength\nalong with your memory, saving dear\nPrince Alfonse would be a simple matter!
Oooo, I'm afraid he sacrificed himself to\nsave you and ended up locked in some\ndark, dank prison. SUCH a shame.
Do not interfere, Hero-King! For if you\nallow us to go, I will have my soldiers\nwithdraw from this town.
...But if you do NOT, I will have them\nraze it to the ground.
I will never allow you to do so!
Uuugh, you are REALLY being difficult!\nOh, fine, then. I guess I'll just have to\nstart by killing...mmmmmm....her!
Thank you for protecting me, but I want\nmy memory back—so stay out of it.
See? This didn't have to be so hard.\nI'm so glad SOMEONE finally saw reason!
Are you certain this was a good idea,\nsir knight?
Hello? Is anyone here? We heard the\nimperial army had invaded this town.
It doesn't seem to have been attacked.
I'm so glad we found you, Prince Marth.
As am I. But now I'm even more upset\nI let Princess Veronica go.
Let me tell you the tale...
Gah! I can't believe Loki beat us here!
My apologies. I should have made\nmore of a clear effort to stop them.
Your judgment saved the people\nof this town. You have my thanks.
Nonetheless, we cannot leave things\nwith Loki and Veronica as they stand.
I bear responsibility for what has\ntranspired. If you mean to search for\nVeronica, pray allow me to aid you.
We'd be happy for the help.
